# ReFrame environment variables. Copy to `.env.local` and fill in as needed.

# --- LLM (copy rewriting) ---------------------------------------------------
# Without a key, generation falls back to deterministic, non-AI copy.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional model override (defaults to a sensible current model).
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=

# --- Data store -------------------------------------------------------------
# Every store (accounts, sites, projects, shares, leads, analytics) picks its
# backend from the environment, in this order of precedence:
#   1. Supabase (Postgres)   - when SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY set
#   2. Vercel KV / Upstash   - when KV_REST_API_URL + KV_REST_API_TOKEN set
#   3. Filesystem (.data/)   - local default, single instance only
# No code change is needed to switch; /api/health reports the active backend.
#
# --- Supabase (recommended for production) ---
# Durable, multi-instance Postgres. Use the SERVICE-ROLE key: the server is the
# only client and it bypasses RLS (every table has RLS on with no policies, so
# the anon/publishable key can read nothing). Apply db/schema.sql to your
# project first (Supabase SQL editor, or `supabase db push`).
# SUPABASE_URL=https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# --- Vercel KV / Upstash Redis (alternative) ---
# REFRAME_DATA_DIR=.data/sites      # override the local data dir if you like
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# --- Headless rendering (read JS-rendered / bot-protected sites) -------------
# STRONGLY RECOMMENDED IN PRODUCTION. Most modern sites are JavaScript-rendered
# or behind bot protection, so a plain fetch sees an empty shell - and the whole
# product's quality is capped by how well we read the source site. Point this at
# a Browserless instance (self-hosted Docker, or the cloud endpoint) and the
# analyzer renders the real page (including SPA shells) before extracting.
# Without it, JS-rendered sites fall back to a generic, industry-templated
# rebuild instead of the client's real content.
#
# Note: the "before" preview screenshot (for sites that refuse to be framed)
# already works with no config via a LOCAL Playwright/Chromium browser. A
# Browserless URL is only needed on hosts that can't run a local browser
# (e.g. some serverless platforms), where it also powers the analyzer's render.
# BROWSERLESS_URL=https://chrome.browserless.io   # or http://localhost:3000 self-hosted
# BROWSERLESS_TOKEN=

# --- Image hosting (owner-uploaded logo + photos) ---------------------------
# Lets owners upload real images for the rebuild (hero, gallery) instead of
# relying on scraped ones. On Vercel: add a Blob store (Storage tab) and this is
# injected automatically. Without it, the photo upload is disabled (the site
# falls back to scraped images / gradients).
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# --- Accounts / sessions ----------------------------------------------------
# Secret used to sign session cookies. Set a long random value in production
# (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`). A dev fallback is used when unset.
# AUTH_SECRET=
#
# Comped accounts (comma-separated emails) treated as the top plan without
# Stripe - for founders/team and for testing the full publish + contact flow.
# ADMIN_EMAILS=you@example.com

# --- Hosting / domains ------------------------------------------------------
# Root domain for branded subdomains. When set, published sites are served at
# <slug>.<root> (e.g. komorebi.reframe.site) and the app resolves them by Host.
# Requires wildcard DNS (*.<root>) pointing at the deployment. Custom domains
# (Pro+) are connected per site and should CNAME to cname.<root>.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ROOT_DOMAIN=reframe.site
#
# Custom domains (Pro+) are registered with the Vercel project via its API so
# they actually route here AND get an automatic TLS certificate. Set a token
# with access to the project and the project id (and team id if it's under a
# team). Without these, connecting a domain falls back to a local DNS check
# only - the domain won't serve real HTTPS traffic until it's added to Vercel.
# VERCEL_API_TOKEN=
# VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=prj_...
# VERCEL_TEAM_ID=team_...        # only if the project lives under a team

# --- Transactional email (Resend) -------------------------------------------
# When set, verification + password-reset emails are delivered via Resend.
# Without it, emails are logged to the server console (dev) so flows still work.
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# EMAIL_FROM=ReFrame <hello@yourdomain.com>

# --- Billing (Stripe) -------------------------------------------------------
# Billing activates only when the secret key, webhook secret and at least the
# Pro price are set. Until then, checkout/portal return a clear "not configured"
# response and the app runs unchanged.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...        # from `stripe listen` or the dashboard
# STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...             # recurring price for Pro
# STRIPE_PRICE_STUDIO=price_...          # recurring price for Studio
